reviews.text: Nice American-style steakhouse with high quality food at a decent price. You'll be likely to find a lot of indulgences here, and it is worth a visit if you're in the market to treat yourself when you are around Fashion Walk in Causeway bay. Lazy weekend brunches here are pretty awesome, and weekday dinners are good too!

I had Eggs Benedict, the salad, soup and a cappuccino. Overall, the salad was great, the soup okay (too strong and salty), the cappuccino was good and the eggs were good. The flavour of the Eggs Benedict was nice, but the bread was too soft and became mushy quickly. The lettuce just made the flavour of the main dish too diluted, like putting water in orange juice.

Would i go again? Yes, but not for the eggs unless I was going with a friend.
Good food for a fair price. Skipped the brunch semi buffet though, since it only included a bit of salad.

The food are good but I waited for the meal for half an hour then they just found didnt prepare my lunch. Lastly, i asked 3 waiters to give me the bill and they didnt say any sorry for me. 

The main point is just few customer in there but the service like this.
Very good food and wine.Open air terrace.

reviews.text: This is a trendy shopping area located conveniently in Causeway Bay. There's a collection of fancy boutiques & clothing stores from various designer labels. The products are pretty high-end, meaning they could be pricier than the average store. Nonetheless, everything feels so glamorous and fashionable. This shopping area should appeal to a young demographic for sure.
Shop staff is friendly introducing the brand and they have nice product designs at KLASSE14 shop.
Small but nicely set up mall.  With Logon & Starbuck on 1st floor, I can spend a whole afternoon here. Clean washrooms on ground level. Convenient for visitors.
It has very good brands that you can't find commonly
Easy to get to & meet up with friends for a light bite & drinks. Really quaint & a nice variety to choose from. Not overly crowded too. A nice mix of eclectic groups of people and visitors.
